p";loader.load(req);}Finally I created a really simply PHP routine and saved it in a file called "SaveXML.php". It simply dumps all of the text which was passed to it from Flash into the "balls.xml" file. Here is the code:<?php// simple routine to save xml file// passed a large string from flash using post methodif (isset($GLOBALS["HTTP_RAW_POST_DATA"])) {$xml = $GLOBALS["HTTP_RAW_POST_DATA"];$file = fopen("balls.xml","wb");fwrite($file, $xml);fclose($file);}?> 